https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-mysql-on-centos-8

1. sudo dnf install mysql-server
2. sudo systemctl start mysqld.service
2.1 sudo systemctl status mysqld
3. sudo systemctl enable mysqld
4. Set root password:
    -> sudo mysql_secure_installation
    -> username root, pwd: e@i-v_1S/Iane12q
4. Test connection : mysqladmin -u root -p version

-----------------
Create New User
-----------------
->  sudo mysql -u root -p
->  CREATE USER 'easybus_db_user'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'Ea&syBusDbUser@625#!';
->  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'easybus_db_user'@'%';
->  FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
->  EXIT; 

Configure Remote Connection:
  /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf.
Adjust bind-address:
Locate the bind-address parameter within the [mysqld] section.
To allow connections from any IP address, change bind-address = 127.0.0.1

